          "id": "marugoto_b1_l7_grammar_3",
          "pattern": "て初めて",
          "meaning": "Indicates that a realization or ability occurs only after, or as a result of, a preceding action.",
          "explanation": "This pattern combines the te-form with 初めて to show sequential causality—that one action must happen before another can be realized or understood. It expresses necessity and sequence, used in both formal and casual contexts to emphasize the importance of the first action.",
          "examples": [
            {
              "japanese": "失敗して初めて、自分の間違いに気づきました。",
              "reading": "しっぱいしてはじめて、じぶんのまちがいにきづきました。",
              "english": "Only after failing did I realize my mistake."
            },
            {
              "japanese": "その映画を見て初めて、その歴史の重要性がわかりました。",
              "reading": "そのえいがをみてはじめて、そのれきしのじゅうようせいがわかりました。",
              "english": "Only after watching that film did I understand the importance of that history."
            },
            {
              "japanese": "大学に行って初めて、勉強の本当の大変さを知りました。",
              "reading": "だいがくにいってはじめて、べんきょうのほんとうのたいへんさをしりました。",
              "english": "Only after starting university did I truly understand how difficult studying is."
            }
